    <p>The 20-30-50 budget split is a widely recognized budgeting guideline that suggests allocating your income into three main categories: 20% for savings, 30% for discretionary spending, and 50% for essentials. Here's why this budget split can be argued to be effective:</p>
    <p>1.</p>
