    <p> - Allocating 30% of your income to discretionary spending allows for flexibility and enjoyment without sacrificing your financial stability or long-term goals.</p>
    <p> - This category gives you the freedom to spend on things that bring you joy and enrich your life while still being mindful of your overall budget.</p>
    <p>3.</p>
    <p>Essentials (50%):</p>
    <p> - Essentials include necessary expenses such as housing, utilities, groceries, transportation, healthcare, and insurance.</p>
    <p> - Allocating 50% of your income to essentials ensures that you cover your basic needs and maintain a comfortable standard of living.</p>
    <p> - This category provides a clear framework for managing essential expenses and helps ensure that you allocate a reasonable portion of your income to necessities.</p>
    <p> __________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________</p>
    <p>Using the 20-30-50 budget split effectively involves the following steps:</p>
    <p> - Calculate Your Income: Determine your total monthly income from all sources.</p>
    <p> - Track Your Expenses: Make a list of all your expenses and categorize them as savings, discretionary spending, or essentials.</p>
